Henceforth war becomes the freeman’s chief and proper work; but even in war the family and local hond still asserts itself. Each ‘ pagus' furnishes a company of the select foot whose agility keeps pace with the mounted warriors in the van ³, - while these horsemen themselves and the whole wedge·like phalanx of the mass behind are grouped by families and clansmen standing shoulder to shoulder ⁴: and even their women accompany the warriors . to the field, not only to tend and heal, but to inspire the brave and upbraid the yielding ⁶.

In connexion with their warfare stood another institution ⁰, noticed by Tacitus as already in full force ⁷, and destined afterwards to affect the framework not only of German but of European society, the* enrolment of young men in the ‘comitatus' of a chief or ‘princeps’ The privilege of keeping such a body may be supposed to have extended to all who borethis title ⁸, but in practice it must manifestly have belonged to those only whose wealth and possessions gave them the means ¹of supporting it, and most of all to the king or leader of the state ⁹, who certainly could alone give a public status to his followerS, while enrolment in its ranks, besides being sought for by many as an honour, must have become the natural refuge of the needy of all ranks and stations ¹⁰.
